MCP server has to be available publically to try with OpenAPI playground etc.
Claude Desktop unfortunately don't have an easy way out. Claude API can do that.

In order for us to decide the first step in Golem, we need to test the transport protocol and messages
of MCP

cloudflared tunnel --url http://localhost:8080 (will get something like this in return:

https://telecom-exam-chances-developer.trycloudflare.com


And try the following


```sh
curl -i -X POST https://telecom-exam-chances-developer.trycloudflare.com/mcp \
           -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
           -H "Accept: application/json" \
           -d '{
         "jsonrpc": "2.0",
         "id": 1,
         "method": "initialize",
         "params": {
           "protocolVersion": "2025-06-18",
           "capabilities": {},
           "clientInfo": {
             "name": "curl-client",
             "version": "1.0.0"
           }
         }
       }'
```

responding with something, most importantly a session-id (mcp-session-id)

```sh

{"id":1,"jsonrpc":"2.0","result":{"capabilities":{"tools":{"listChanged":false}},"protocolVersion":"2025-06-18","serverInfo":{"name":"golem-mcp-dev","version":"0.1.0"}}}⏎

```

```sh
curl -X POST https://telecom-exam-chances-developer.trycloudflare.com/mcp \
           -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
           -H "Accept: application/json" \
           -H "Mcp-Session-Id: 59330286-0795-41e5-b952-4b64d618225a" \
           -d '{
         "jsonrpc": "2.0",
         "id": 2,
         "method": "tools/list",
         "params": {}
       }'
{"id":2,"jsonrpc":"2.0","result":{"tools":[{"description":"Returns a greeting","inputSchema":{"properties":{"name":{"type":"string"}},"required":["name"],"type":"object"},"name":"hello_agent","title":"Hello Agent"}]}}⏎
 ~ 

```